Flask (Web Development) 

Flask helps you create websites using Python.

1. Install Flask
pip install flask

2. First Flask App
Program
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return "Hello World"

app.run(debug=True)
Output

Open browser → go to:

http://127.0.0.1:5000/

You will see:

Hello World

3. Multiple Pages
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return "Home Page"

@app.route("/about")
def about():
    return "About Page"

app.run(debug=True)
Output
/ → Home Page
/about → About Page

4. Dynamic Route
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/user/<name>")
def user(name):
    return "Hello " + name

app.run(debug=True)
Output

Open:

http://127.0.0.1:5000/user/Sanjana

Output:

Hello Sanjana

5. HTML Page (Template)
app.py
from flask import Flask, render_template

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return render_template("index.html")

app.run(debug=True)
templates/index.html
<h1>Hello from HTML</h1>
Output

Browser shows:

Hello from HTML

6. Form Input
from flask import Flask, request

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/", methods=["GET", "POST"])
def home():
    if request.method == "POST":
        name = request.form["name"]
        return "Hello " + name
    return '''
        <form method="post">
            <input name="name">
            <input type="submit">
        </form>
    '''

app.run(debug=True)
Input (Browser)

User enters:

Sanjana
Output
Hello Sanjana

7. Simple Web App (Mini Project)
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return "<h1>My First Website</h1>"

@app.route("/contact")
def contact():
    return "Contact us at example@gmail.com"

app.run(debug=True)
